Class Project

java.lang.Object
pm.core.Project
public final class Project extends Object
Represents a project registered in ProjectManager.

A project contains:

  • Unique identifying name
  • Path in the file system
  • Project type (Gradle, Maven, etc.)
  • Map of available commands (build, run, test, etc.)
  • Last modification timestamp

The class is immutable in its core fields (name, path, type). Commands can be added/modified dynamically.

Usage example: 

Path projectPath = Paths.get("/home/user/myapp");
Project project = new Project("myapp", projectPath, ProjectType.GRADLE);
project.addCommand("build", "gradle build");
project.addCommand("run", "gradle run");

String buildCmd = project.getCommand("build"); // "gradle build"

  • Field Details

    • name

      private final String name
      Unique project name. Used as an identifier to execute commands (e.g., pm build myapp). Immutable after creation.

    • path

      private final Path path
      Absolute project path in the file system. Points to the root directory of the project. Immutable after creation.

    • type

      private final ProjectType type
      Project type (Gradle, Maven, Node.js, etc.). Determines which default commands are used. Immutable after creation.

    • commands

      private final Map<String,String> commands
      Map of available commands for this project. Key: command name (e.g., "build", "run", "test") Value: shell command to execute (e.g., "gradle build") Can be modified using addCommand() and removeCommand().

    • lastModified

      private Instant lastModified
      Timestamp of the project's last modification. Automatically updated when commands are added or removed.

    • envVars

      private Map<String,String> envVars

      public void addCommand(String commandName, String commandLine)
      Adds a command to the project. If a command with the same name already exists, it is overwritten. Automatically updates the modification timestamp.
      Parameters:
      commandName - command name (e.g., "build", "run")
      commandLine - command line to execute (e.g., "gradle build")
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if any parameter is null
